# =============================================================================
# FUTURE AUTOPSY (CASE/UCO) OUTPUT — UTAH ICAC TASK FORCE DF EXAMINATION
# =============================================================================
#
# PURPOSE
# - This file represents a *later* digital forensics examination (Autopsy CASE/UCO-style output)
#   performed AFTER the police intelligence repository already contained the Dominic Christensen
#   intelligence graph (`examples_knowledge_graphs/utah-dominic-christensen-example.ttl`).
# - It is structured to demonstrate KG exploitation/enrichment: Autopsy findings (device artifacts)
#   are cross-referenced against a police intelligence graph to enrich the examiner’s context,
#   showing Dominic Christensen is a known recidivist offender.
#
# IMPORTANT NOTE (DEMO INTENT)
# - Autopsy itself may not emit all enrichment triples; the “cross-graph enrichment” section below
#   models a follow-on analytic step performed by the examiner (or an automated KG service) using
#   the examiner’s Autopsy-derived observables.
#
# =============================================================================
# EXAMINER + TASK FORCE CONTEXT
# =============================================================================

kb:org-utah-icac-task-force a uco-identity:Organization ;
    rdfs:label "Utah ICAC Task Force"@en .

